00:37:04.150 --> 00:37:05.810
you don't get paid very much to do this,

00:37:05.810 --> 00:37:07.907
this really complex work, and it's really,

00:37:07.907 --> 00:37:09.616
and it's hard stuff.

00:37:09.616 --> 00:37:12.630
Universities should be
able to take this on.

00:37:12.630 --> 00:37:16.240
They have residents and
fellows and it'd be a great way

00:37:16.240 --> 00:37:20.070
but and once, my
university at UCSD does not

00:37:20.070 --> 00:37:22.740
want to see more than 7% Medicaid.

00:37:22.740 --> 00:37:25.964
That's their goal, and
I don't know what to say

00:37:25.964 --> 00:37:27.800
and that's just, that's
just the way it is.

00:37:27.800 --> 00:37:30.220
So, that's why I see all these patients.

00:37:30.220 --> 00:37:32.010
We need to get some lifespan physicians

00:37:32.010 --> 00:37:34.550
and I think that's possibly coming

00:37:34.550 --> 00:37:37.540
and I think as we start doing things in

00:37:39.580 --> 00:37:41.700
our CP academy and some
of our schools that

00:37:41.700 --> 00:37:42.820
